cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a heterogeneous MapReduce computing system and the tradeoff between computation and communication in a distributed setting. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions coded multicasting opportunities and achieving an achievable communication load. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is relevant as the paper discusses communication load and file allocation strategies in a distributed computing system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes function assignments and file allocation strategies to optimize the performance of the system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses partitioning input files into disjoint batches and computing additional files from non-computed files.
